<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Bull &amp; Bear Group Inc., a manager of mutual
funds, said it terminated efforts to seek a buyer or an
equity partner in a joint venture arrangement for its fund
management business.
   Bassett S. Winmill, chairman of Bull &amp; Bear, said, "While
we received numerous expressions of interest, acceptable
terms could not be negotiated which would be in the best
long-term interests of both our employees and our
shareholders."
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company manages about $345 million in fund assets.
</TEXT>
