<LP>
   CARMEL, Calif. -- Landmark Land Co. said its $60 million
contract to sell resort assets at Carmel Valley Ranch to
American International Golf Resorts Inc. has been terminated.
The sale would have yielded Landmark a $20 million profit.
   The assets included the Carmel Valley Ranch resort, golf
course and tennis club.
